<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-10-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-10-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="284" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d284">
                    <head>No. 280.<lb/><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to
                            King <persName type="to">Kaldkaua</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Executive
                                    Mansion</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>,
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-10-11"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 11, 1886</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p rend="flushleft">To His Majesty <hi rend="smallcaps">Kalakaua</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Honolulu, via San Francisco:</hi></p>
                    <p>Your Majesty’s kind words of sympathy are no less gratifying to the people of
                        this country than to me, and in their name I thank you.</p>
                    <closer><signed>GROYER CLEVELAND.</signed></closer>
                </div>
            </body></text></TEI>